        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Suppose that V is a k-plane in R\". Denote the hyperplanes {Xn = 0} and {n = 1) by Vo and Vi, respectively. If V nVo and V ^Vi are each at most (k - 1)dimensional, then V NVoNZ and V NV, NZ each have cardinality at most 2k-' by the induction assumption, and hence V ^Z has at most 2' elements. Otherwise, if n% or V NV, is k-dimensional, then V C Vo or VC Vi; now apply the induction hypothesis on V, viewed as a subset of R\"-' by dropping the last coordinate.",
        "bbox": [
