        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Second solution: Let S be a subset of Z contained in a k-dimensional subspace of V. This is equivalent to asking that any 11,..., Ik+1 € S satisfy a nontrivial linear dependence c11+... +ck+1+1 = 0 with c1,..., Ck+1 E R. Since 11,..., Ek+1 E Q\", given such a dependence we can always find another one with c1,..., Ck+1 E Q; then by clearing denominators, we can find one with C1,..., Ck+1 E Z and not all having a common factor.",
        "bbox": [
