        "text": "Let Ez denote the field of two elements, and let S C Fy be the reductions modulo 2 of the points of S. Then any 11,..., k+1 ES satisfy a nontrivial linear dependence, because we can take the dependence from the end of the previous paragraph and reduce modulo 2. Hence S is contained in a k-dimensional subspace of Ez, and the latter has cardinality exactly 2k · Thus S has at most 2k elements, as does S.",
